Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Prep roundup: Tigers claim 4th straight section title TIMES STAFF REPORT 10:43 p.m. CDT October 16, 2015 Sports brief (Photo: Times graphic) 
SARTELL — Taylor Tarrolly added two more wins to her record-breaking career total at Fitness Evolution on Friday as she led the Tigers to a Section 8-2A championship and a berth in the Class 2A state tournament. 
The Tigers defeated Thief River Falls 6-1 to capture their fourth straight section title. Tech blanked Bemidji 7-0 in the semifinal match to get to the championship match. 
Tarrolly, who has 128 career victories, was 2-0 on the day at No. 1 singles. 
Katelyn Tarrolly and Ashley Tarrolly also were 2-0 at second and third singles, respectively. 
Kate Inderieden played No. 4 singles and was 2-0 for Tech. 
Rebekah Zwiener and Anne Bowe teamed up at No. 1 doubles and collected two wins for the Tigers. 
“I think (the team) is looking forward to the opportunity to be playing in the state tournament,” coach Paul Bates said. “Its another goal the team achieved.” 
The state tournament begins Oct. 27 at Baseline Tennis Center in Minneapolis. 
VOLLEYBALL 
ROCHESTER — Senior Kyra Harvey had 10 kills Friday in Sauk Rapids’ two matches. 
The Storm defeated Plainview-Elgin-Millville 2-0 (25-21, 25-22) and were defeated by Rochester-Mayo 2-0 (25-18, 25-16). 
Morgan Held had a combined 15 set assists and four ace serves for Sauk Rapids (6-4 Central Lakes, 14-8 overall).
